{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7b6e6bd4-c3da-401a-862e-e0f6d5f4a620","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_019vjpT81F3KygXt39wP9VwN","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Answering MSTest SDK question"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01GDif9LminwErf9sApZSzb3","name":"view","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-bf3f9556cc474272a4b617bd0b986eb2"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"view the file at /tmp/sv-bf3f9556cc474272a4b617bd0b986eb2."}],"interactionId":"be7d729f-1c66-4699-90ff-da3f808492ba","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a breaking change between MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0 and MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0 related to test discovery with vstest.console. This is a knowledge question about MSTest SDK changes, not a code investigation task.\n\nLet me look at the files in the working directory to understand context, but this is primarily a knowledge-based question.\n\nI know that MSTest.Sdk 4.x made a significant breaking change: it defaults to using Microsoft.Testing.Platform (the new test runner) instead of VSTest. When using Microsoft.Testing.Platform as the default, the test assemblies are built as executables that run tests directly, and vstest.console can no longer discover/run them because they don't expose the VSTest adapter interfaces in the same way.\n\n\nThe core issue is that MSTest.Sdk 4.x switched to Microsoft.Testing.Platform by default, whereas 3.x still defaulted to VSTest. This means tests built with 4.x are compiled for the new platform runner and won't be discoverable by vstest.console unless you explicitly revert to VSTest compatibility mode.\n\nThe solution is straightforward: either migrate your CI pipeline to use `dotnet test` instead, which works with both runners, or add `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` to your project file to restore VSTest support. Let me look at what's in the directory to understand the setup better.","outputTokens":541,"requestId":"67C0:58623:1D87704:2128867:69FD547A"},"id":"ca2fb25c-5230-4ede-a9e1-f89a694548bf","timestamp":"2026-05-08T03:12:07.690Z","parentId":"7c4b2573-29dd-4c68-8276-76ee0b51c2b2"}
