{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"832df750-57ff-4735-a2a8-b40a424758aa","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform exclusively.** That's the breaking change.\n\nIn 3.x, the SDK still built VSTest-compatible test assemblies, so `vstest.console` could discover and run them. Starting with 4.x, it enables the new Microsoft.Testing.Platform runner by default and **drops VSTest adapter support**, meaning `vstest.console` finds zero tests.\n\n### You have two options:\n\n**Option A — Switch your CI to `dotnet test` (recommended):**\n```\ndotnet test TestProject.csproj\n```\n`dotnet test` works with both runners and is the supported path going forward.\n\n**Option B — Opt back into VSTest compatibility:**\nAdd this to your `.csproj`:\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\nThis re-enables the VSTest adapters so `vstest.console` can discover tests again, but you lose the new platform features.\n\nWould you like me to update your project file with either option?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"be7d729f-1c66-4699-90ff-da3f808492ba","outputTokens":253,"requestId":"67C1:2D5697:1C1A53A:1FBF9C6:69FD5488"},"id":"b7f1e5f5-29d0-47f0-bb2a-5ece5946d16f","timestamp":"2026-05-08T03:12:15.267Z","parentId":"94440af1-6a84-4c2b-bc58-e3269a2e3e0d"}
